---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="House Painters Sandy Bay | Heritage & Weatherboard"
  description="House painters in Sandy Bay — heritage and weatherboard homes, lead-safe prep on pre-1970 stock, interior and premium exterior repaints. Cold-climate prep, low-VOC paints. Free quote."
  canonical="https://hobarthousepainters.com.au/sandy-bay/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Sandy Bay &middot; Battery Point &middot; Lower Sandy Bay</span>
      <h1>House painters in <span class="accent">Sandy Bay</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Sandy Bay is heritage-home country &mdash; gracious older houses and
        weatherboard cottages, a lot of it pre-1970 and carrying lead paint, set
        on the western shore of the Derwent. It calls for careful, lead-safe
        preparation and premium repaints that handle the salt air and the cold,
        damp climate. That&rsquo;s exactly the work we do here.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Sandy Bay</span>
      <h2>Painting Sandy Bay homes.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Heritage and pre-1970 stock = lead paint.</h3>
        <p>
          A large share of Sandy Bay and neighbouring Battery Point is older
          housing &mdash; Federation and Georgian homes, weatherboard cottages,
          gracious brick residences &mdash; much of it built well before 1970.
          That means the existing paint is very likely <strong>lead-based</strong>.
          We prepare these homes to AS 4361.2 lead-safe practice: no dry sanding
          that throws lead dust across the garden, proper containment, and clean
          collection of debris. It&rsquo;s the part of the job a cheap quote
          quietly skips &mdash; and the part that protects your family. More on
          our <a href="/services/heritage-painting/">heritage &amp; weatherboard
          painting</a> page.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Salt off the Derwent and a damp aspect.</h3>
        <p>
          Sandy Bay sits right on the river. Exterior elevations cop salt-laden
          air and the suburb&rsquo;s cool, often-shaded blocks stay damp, which
          feeds mould on weatherboard and render. Our exterior process starts
          with a proper wash and mould treatment before any sanding or coating,
          and we use paints rated for cool, damp maritime conditions so the
          finish actually lasts the <strong>7&ndash;10 year</strong> Hobart
          repaint cycle rather than peeling early. See
          <a href="/services/exterior-painting/">exterior house painting</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Premium interiors for a premium suburb.</h3>
        <p>
          Sandy Bay homeowners expect a high-end interior finish &mdash; neat
          cut-ins, smooth ceilings, properly prepared period trim and joinery.
          We use low-VOC paints (better in a closed-up winter home) and protect
          original floorboards and features carefully throughout. On older homes
          we keep lead-safe practice indoors too, where sanding old trim could
          release dust. See <a href="/services/interior-painting/">interior house
          painting</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heritage precinct? Worth a check first.</h3>
        <p>
          Parts of Sandy Bay and Battery Point sit in heritage-sensitive areas.
          A like-for-like repaint is usually fine, but a change of colour scheme
          on a listed place or within a City of Hobart heritage precinct can
          touch planning rules. We&rsquo;ll flag whether your job is
          straightforward and keep the work sympathetic to the period either way.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Sandy Bay jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Lead-safe exterior repaint of a pre-1970 weatherboard cottage</li>
          <li>Full heritage repaint of a Federation or Georgian home, period-correct scheme</li>
          <li>Premium interior repaint with careful protection of original floors and trim</li>
          <li>Render and trim refresh on a river-facing home exposed to salt air</li>
          <li>Roof clean and recoat to lift a tired tile or metal roof</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/glenorchy/">Glenorchy</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/kingston/">Kingston</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/moonah/">Moonah</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/new-town/">New Town</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hobart-region/">All Greater Hobart</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Sandy Bay painting quote.</h2>
        <p>Heritage and weatherboard specialists. Lead-safe prep. Premium interior and exterior finish.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
